Your Turn 3

  1. mutate() -> This is generally safe because all it is doing is creating a new variable
  2. arrange() -> This is generally safe because all of the data is still there just in a new order
  3. filter() -> This is generally not safe because it will remove some data that does not fit the parameters that we are filtering by. You would have to be sure that you will never need access to the rows that you filter out again.
  4. summarise() -> This is generally not safe because youâre changing the structure of the data to be only one row per group and you lose access to the original data
  5. select() -> This is generally not safe because it will remove columns that you do not select. You would have to be sure that you will never need access to the rows that you filter out again.
